Ad Text:
Harvey Norman’s Information Technology Department’s core focus is to deliver innovative IT solutions by delivering crucial projects to achieve the strategic goals of the business.

We have recently embarked on a journey to streamline processes, reduce technological complexity, and boost efficiency within our people management systems. This initiative will improve people data management, compliance, visibility and analytics, productivity, and employee engagement for approximately 15,000 people across Australia and New Zealand.

About the role  

This is a fantastic opportunity to be part of a large scale, complex HCM transformation. Joining a multi-disciplinary agile team, working closely with Technology, WFM/Payroll and HR leads, you will be responsible for leading business requirements & process analysis, and developing & executing test scenarios, focusing on Dayforce Implementation on downstream systems. 

This is Full Time Maximum Term Contract for up to 12 months, with an ideal commencement date in the first week of February 2026.

You will;

Requirements Gathering: Assist the WFM/Payroll & HR lead and collaborate with stakeholders to review, gather, document, and prioritise business requirements related to Dayforce implementation impacts of any downstream systems.
Business Process Analysis: Assist the WFM/Payroll lead, HR lead and Technology SME’s in analysing existing and future state business processes of downstream systems, identify areas for improvement in alignment with Dayforce capabilities, project team and SI partner. Facilitate stakeholder meetings to drive requirements, consider alternatives and negotiate project outcomes within milestone timeframes.
Testing: Work closely with both the Dayforce and Technology leads to assist & execute SIT/End-to-End testing, including documenting integration & downstream system test scenarios, validating errors or adjustments to user stories/acceptance criteria test scripts.
Detailed Procedure Documentation: Work closely with internal Payroll, WFM, technology SME’s, project leads and SI partner functional consultants to contribute to & review detailed administrator procedures for using Technology related administration related to the Integration services and all downstream systems
Team Support and Collaboration: Foster cross-team collaboration to help project team members complete project tasks and produce deliverables. Participate in your team's operating rhythm and provide progress updates through agreed forums and channels.

About you  

You will have extensive experience as a Senior Business Analyst in a similar role, with a proven track record of successfully delivering large complex IT projects. You will bring strong analytical thinking and problem-solving skills, enabling you to lead workshops, guide discussions, and provide insightful analysis for your projects. You’ll also have a keen ability to identify opportunities for improvement and drive meaningful change.

You will also have: 

Experience working on HR/Payroll/WFM projects across any ERP
Experience in writing business and project documentation to support the implementation of technology solutions.
Excellent written and verbal communication, with the ability to effectively communicate with business stakeholders.
Knowledge of project management lifecycles and product implementation methodologies (waterfall, agile, hybrid).
Proficiency in asking insightful questions to uncover the underlying reasons behind stakeholder processes.
Strong ability to manage multiple initiatives simultaneously and prioritise competing deadlines.
Expertise in the management and execution of end-to-end system testing
Ability to partner effectively with the business to ensure outcomes align with business needs and objectives.
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business or Engineering.

This opportunity will provide: 

Access to Udemy, an online training platform with over 5,500 courses.
Experience working with an Iconic Australian Brand with global success in NZ, Asia, and Europe.
A supportive team environment that celebrates diversity and promotes a healthy work and family life balance. 
Opportunities to make discounted purchases on a great range of products and services.

Have we got your interest?  

Apply now to be considered to join our dedicated team.  

Please note that only people with the right to work in Australia should apply for this position.  

Recruitment Agencies – thank you for thinking of us, however we do endeavour to fill our opportunities through direct channels wherever possible. If we find that we do need agency assistance, we’ll be in touch.

Perigon Group is proudly partnering with a leading national property group to recruit a newly created Senior Business Analyst within their Brisbane CBD office.

This ASX-listed organisation is known for its stability, strong governance, and people-centred culture. You’ll be joining a group with a significant national footprint, a top-tier team of professionals, and a culture that values collaboration, integrity, and long-term career growth.

The Role

In this role, you will operate at the core of project analytics, financial modelling and reporting accuracy. You’ll work closely with project and operational teams to ensure data integrity, strengthen financial capability across the development function and provide insights that support senior leadership and board-level decision-making. The work is hands-on, varied and commercially meaningful.

Key Responsibilities

• Develop and refine financial models including cash flow, P&L, balance sheet and scenario analysis.
• Deliver accurate reporting, forecasting and budget inputs across multiple development portfolios.
• Support and coach Development Managers and junior project staff on financial terminology and assumptions.
• Review and enhance system modules and data inputs within internal platforms (Excel, Power Query and BI tools).
• Provide clear, commercially minded insights in a collaborative, people-focused environment.

About You

• Strong financial modelling capability with advanced Excel skill (Power BI, Power Query very beneficial).
• Experience in financial analysis or commercial finance within project-based or complex operating environments.
• Confident educating and influencing non-financial stakeholders.
• High attention to detail and accuracy, with the ability to operate effectively in a lean, fast-paced team.
• A warm, low-ego communication style aligned to a people-centric culture.

Why This Role Stands Out

• A compelling opportunity for technically strong, commercially minded finance professionals seeking genuine influence.
• High-impact involvement in shaping project outcomes and partnering closely with senior leaders.
• Key role in lifting financial capability across development teams.
• For property-experienced candidates: broader exposure, deeper ownership of modelling and cross-state collaboration.
• For candidates from other industries: an opportunity to apply analytical strengths while learning a project-driven sector within a supportive, well-established finance team.
• Join a values-led group with a people-first culture, collaborative national team, flexible working arrangements and a strong suite of benefits.

Please apply using the links below. For a confidential discussion or further information, please contact Haydn Furness at Perigon Group Brisbane on (07) 3854 3805 or haydn.furness@perigongroup.com.au.

Proven ability to translate business requirements into actionable functional and technical specifications.
Solid experience working with integration patterns, APIs, data migration concepts, and system interfaces.
Strong ERP project delivery background, ideally across major transformation or platform rollout programs.
Experience in one or more ERP functional domains (e.g., supply chain, finance, inventory, retail operations).
Proficiency with Jira, Confluence, and other documentation tools.
Strong understanding of testing frameworks, test scripting, and defect lifecycle management.
Experience collaborating with developers, test leads, architects, and operational stakeholders.

Excellent stakeholder engagement, communication, and documentation skills.

About Us

From humble beginnings in 2011, Evolution Mining is now a leading gold producer, operating six mines across Australia and Canada. Enacting our vision to be inspired people creating a premier global gold company, we are indeed a bold team with a bright future. Our operational diversity offers our employees access to many experiences and career opportunities within the one company. So, whether you choose to work at one of our underground or open pit operations, explore for our future as part of our Discovery team, or join our Group Office, we know you'll have a bright future with us.

At our Group Office

Working in our Group office, you have a front row seat to our vision and are a part of the bold, inspired teams who are engineering its success. We're an agile, entrepreneurial company and we value smart people and creative thinking. Based in the Sydney CBD, our people work with teams located across Australia and Canada, which makes for interesting work and countless ways to learn and grow.

Your Benefits

At Evolution, we support, develop and reward everyone who chooses to be a part of our bright future. Your benefits include relocation support assistance, novated car leasing, life insurance and income protection, short term incentives, referral bonuses, recognition program, study assistance, discounted health insurance and wellness days. 

This roster is 5/2 (Monday to Friday) and a 8 hour day.

Please note: Initially, we expect office attendance to support onboarding and collaboration, with flexibility discussed once you've completed your probation period.

We understand that flexible work means something different to everyone and encourage you to have a conversation about the flexible work options available.

About the Role

Step into a fixed term role that puts you at the heart of Evolution Mining's story. As Analyst - Investor Relations, you'll be part of a small, high-performing team that works closely with C-Suite and senior leadership to shape how we engage with the investment community. This isn't just about numbers, it's about creating narratives that influence market perception and build trust.

You'll combine analytical skills with creativity, turning complex data into clear, impactful messaging. From preparing investor presentations to coordinating roadshows and conferences, you'll have a front-row seat to strategic decision-making and exposure few roles can offer.

In this role, you will:

Craft presentations, ASX releases, and reports that showcase Evolution's performance and vision.
Coordinate investor meetings, conferences, and roadshows, ensuring flawless execution.
Analyse competitor performance and market trends to provide insights for senior management.

About You

You're not just detail-oriented, you're curious, adaptable, and ready to make an impact. With a foundation in Commerce, Finance, Law, Mining or a related discipline, you bring strong analytical skills and a talent for turning complex information into clear, engaging narratives. You're comfortable working with senior stakeholders and thrive in environments where priorities shift quickly. Experience in financial markets or investor relations is ideal, but we value adaptability and a willingness to learn.

You'll stand out if you:

Have advanced PowerPoint and Word skills and enjoy creating polished, professional presentations.
Are proactive, organised, and confident communicating with different audiences.
Are motivated by opportunities to learn about financial markets and gain exposure to C-Suite decision-making.

If you're looking for a role that blends analysis, creativity, and strategic influence, and gives you a front-row seat to the investment community, this is your chance.

Closing

At Evolution, as our name suggests, change and transformation is in our DNA. We want the Evolution experience to be your career highlight. We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a more inclusive and diverse workforce that represents the communities in which we operate. We provide a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all and candidates from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. We are focused on keeping our people safe and healthy and creating sustainable value in an environmentally and socially responsible way. Join our bold team to start your next exciting chapter.

To Apply

To find out more about us click here: https://joinus.evolutionmining.com/
We thank you for taking the time to submit your application.

About the opportunity


Data Governance/Cleansing Lead

Location: Melbourne

Jan 2026 start – until end of September 2026 – view to extend until September 2027




Are you passionate about driving data quality at scale? We’re seeking a Data Governance /Cleansing Lead to take ownership of cleansing standards and ensure our transformation program delivers clean, trusted, and compliant data.

 

Key Responsibilities:

Challenge and validate: Evaluate vendor cleansing plans, methodologies, and tools to ensure alignment with enterprise standards and business expectations.

Enforce governance: Ensure all cleansing activities comply with data governance policies, regulatory requirements, and security standards.

Set the bar for quality: Define and enforce data quality rules, thresholds, and validation protocols across legacy and target systems.

Collaborate and resolve: Work closely with vendors, data owners, SMEs, and external partners to coordinate cleansing activities and resolve data quality issues.

Monitor and measure: Partner with the Performance Reporting Dashboard Lead and Senior Consultant to establish metrics and dashboards tracking cleansing progress and issue resolution.

Manage risk: Identify and escalate risks related to data integrity and cleansing scope, and work with stakeholders to define mitigation strategies.

Document and report: Maintain clear documentation of cleansing processes, standards, and decisions to support auditability and governance.




Required skills and experience:

Proven experience leading data governance and cleansing initiatives in large-scale programs.

Strong understanding of data governance, compliance, and security standards.

Ability to challenge vendors constructively and influence outcomes.

Excellent stakeholder engagement and problem-solving skills.

Familiarity with data quality tools, metrics, and reporting frameworks.

 

Why Join Us?

This is your opportunity to lead a critical workstream in a major transformation program, ensuring data integrity and enabling business success.

Apply now and help us deliver clean, trusted data for the future

About XO Sports

At XO Sports, we’re redefining the game by giving bettors the edge over the bookies. Sitting at the intersection of advanced mathematics, predictive data science, machine learning, and the global sports betting economy, our platform delivers the analytical power bettors need to operate with confidence, discipline, and consistency.

We process millions of data points and run thousands of match simulations to produce a single, clear, easy-to-use prediction—giving punters intellectual depth without the complexity.

The Opportunity

We have an exciting opening for a Project Manager / Business Analyst with strong technical and analytical skills to join our growing team.

What You’ll Do

Partner with SMEs, tech teams, process owners, and business stakeholders to define scope, requirements, and outcomes.

Manage end-to-end delivery of sports and technology features, leveraging your project management expertise and Jira skills.

Create and maintain high-quality documentation, reporting, RAID logs, governance packs, and delivery artefacts.

Facilitate workshops, drive clarity, and provide deeper analysis where required.

Identify and manage risks, issues, and dependencies, ensuring timely communication to stakeholders.

Coordinate across multiple technology teams within a complex data and data science ecosystem.

Ensure initiatives align with broader organisational strategy and capability uplift objectives.

What We’re Looking For

Proven experience as a Project Manager, ideally with hands-on Business Analysis experience.

Background in delivering frameworks, standards, capability uplift, regulatory, operating model, risk, or process improvement initiatives.

Ability to work across multiple technology teams and manage competing priorities.

Strong stakeholder engagement and alignment-building skills.

Highly organised, structured thinker with a proactive approach to delivery.

Willingness to “roll up your sleeves” for deeper analysis or documentation when needed.

Highly Regarded: Experience in data, analytics, technology, or machine learning environments.

Why XO Sports?

If you’re a delivery-focused Project Manager who thrives on structure, frameworks, and cutting-edge sports technology, this is your chance to join a team that’s shaping the future of sports betting.

You’ll be part of an integrated Intelligen consulting team, working closely with our architects, senior consultants, and client-side technical stakeholders. This role is ideal for engineers who are hands-on, delivery-driven, and comfortable working in fast-moving, iterative project environments.

What You’ll Do
Re-engineer and refactor existing dbt models to align with domain-driven design principles.
Optimise and uplift existing Snowflake datasets, data structures, and transformation pipelines
Contribute to solution design, technical decisions, and modelling best practices
Work closely with client data teams to ensure maintainability, performance, and clarity of lineage.
Support CI/CD, testing, and documentation of all aspects of data engineering projects.
Collaborate with the broader Intelligen consulting practice as part of a multi-resource delivery team.
Contribute to ongoing consulting engagements beyond the initial project as part of our integrated consulting pool.


Requirements


3–5+ years’ experience in data engineering or analytics engineering roles.
Strong, hands-on ETL expertise
Solid Snowflake experience, including schema design, performance tuning, and warehousing best practices.
Ideally experience with SQL, data modelling (dimensional/domain), and modern data stack tooling.
Ability to operate in “doer mode” — comfortable rolling up sleeves and delivering quickly in line with agreed standards
Consulting experience is a plus but not required; strong communication and problem-solving skills are essential.


Must-have's...

Advanced dbt capability (the strongest requirement)
Strong, practical Snowflake engineering experience
Ability to deliver independently within a structured consulting engagement.



Benefits



We’re not just delivering AI and data projects.. we’re humanising them. That means we care deeply about the how, not just the what. We value curiosity, creativity, and a willingness to challenge the status quo. We look for people who are driven to build a business, get curious, and offer opinions and ideas.

You’ll join a team that’s smart, kind, and ambitious. You’ll have real influence - in your projects, your practice, and the broader business. And as we grow, so will you.

Here’s what that looks like:

Grow With Purpose

Structured development pathways so you always know what you’re working toward.
Paid certifications across all major cloud and data technologies — because mastery matters
Weekly training, guilds and knowledge exchanges where practitioners share real project insights.


Support That Helps You Thrive

A dedicated support lead to mentor, guide and help you navigate your career
Regular 360° feedback loops, giving you clear direction and honest insight into your progress.


A Community You’ll Enjoy Being Part Of

Innovation days where you can experiment, prototype and sharpen new skills.
Team days, social catchups,  many new community clubs…
Opportunities to lead, influence and shape our growing practice as we expand across the region.


If you want to be part of a team that cares just as much about how we deliver as what we deliver; where curiosity is valued, ideas matter, and your impact is felt - drop us a message and start the conversation today...

Ad Text:
Hybrid work environment

10-month max-term contract

Play a fundamental role in implementing a new Procurement Strategy to enhance risk and digitise processes, tools, and AI adoption



About the business/role/team

Join a forward-thinking team within the Bank's Procurement function, driving innovation and efficiency through digital enablement. You will report to the Strategic Sourcing Manager and work closely with the Head of Procurement, procurement specialists, technology teams, and customers business wide.

About the role

Support the roll out of the new Procurement Strategy which is underpinned by digitisation of processes and tools.

Design and implement a Copilot-based procurement chatbot working closely with customers on the user experience, knowledge management, and logic.

Lead the drafting of governance policies and guidelines relating to procurement, probity, and related risk and connected policies

Support a Contract Management System implementation including requirements traceability, workflow design, testing, and go-live activities.

Identify data sources and build dashboards for KPIs, KRIs, and performance tracking.

Redesign processes for efficiency and improved end-user experience.

Develop and execute change management and communications materials.

Engage stakeholders to ensure smooth adoption of new processes and tools.

About you

Familiarity with procurement processes (buyer or seller side)

Familiarity using a Contract Management System

Familiar with using Copilot and a keen mind to leverage AI to support every day work.

Proficiency in data analytics, dashboard creation.

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills.

Experience in Analysis or Consulting roles such as Data Analyst, Business Analyst, Product Owner, Strategy Analyst, Senior Consultant, Manager Consultant

Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Finance Business Partner – Global Brands | Partner with Marketing to Drive Impact

Make your mark. Change the game. Join the pack.


Ready to take your analytical skills beyond the numbers? At RPF we are in an exciting Transformational Phase and have targeted the next 2 years to expand and grow our brands globally. 

As a result, we have a newly created opportunity for a passionate and commercially savvy Finance Business Partner who thrives at the intersection of marketing, commercial strategy, and consumer impact to support the business in being consumer led. 

We are bringing our brands into focus, and you will play a key role in helping us achieve this goal.

In this role, you’ll do more than budgets and reports — you’ll be a true analytical partner to Marketing, developing insights and providing analysis that will help shape brand campaigns, new product launches, and consumer engagement initiatives with sharp financial insight. 

From forecasting global brand spend to building business cases for innovation, you’ll influence decisions that change the game and keep our brands ahead of the pack.

What you’ll do:

Lead budgeting, forecasting, and reporting to maximise brand investment and ROI.
Partner with Marketing leaders on campaign strategy, promotions, and innovation.
Build financial models and scenario analyses to guide commercial decisions.
Leverage data and tech to simplify reporting and automate insights.
Foster a performance-driven culture, coaching both finance and non-finance teams to use data in decision-making.




What we’re looking for:

Proven ability as a Finance Business Partner within a commercial, fast-paced environment
You are a commercially sharp individual who could have developed your career up from being a qualified accountant into commercial accounting/analyst positions.
CA/CPA/CIMA Qualified preferred but not essential 
Experience working across marketing, sales, or FMCG/consumer goods preferred.
Someone who balances financial discipline with creativity and commercial flair.
A collaborator who embodies our values: Work as a Pack, Make Your Mark, Lead with Passion, and Change the Game.




This is your chance to step into the spotlight, directly influencing how global brands connect with consumers, while growing your career in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.




What we’re about

Welcome to RPF, where we believe in keeping it Real.

Since 1994, we have been Australia and New Zealand’s pioneers in fresher dog and cat nutrition. Our story is one of passion for a better way to care for pets, a belief in fresher nutrition, and an unwavering commitment to delivering this to pet parents and pets worldwide.

We're dedicated to fostering authentic partnerships, encouraging real ambition, and providing real career opportunities for our employees to make a difference.

Real means fresher ingredients and fresher methods. We'll never stop expanding, innovating, and trying new things. We compete in every pet category and channel, creating favourite brands such as Ivory Coat, Nature’s Gift, V.I.P. Petfoods, and Love ‘Em & Fussy Cat!

Since the establishment of RPF, we have grown to over 900 people across Australia and New Zealand, China, Southeast Asia and Europe.

With the pet industry growing rapidly (a $15 billion industry!) and pets becoming increasingly important in our lives and homes, this is a unique opportunity to be a part of our remarkable growth story and advance your career.




Why join us?

Do work that matters. We’re pioneering in a new area of pet food, always striving for fresher. We’re restless, creating a better life for our pets.

Make an impact and change the game. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to do your best work – and to make a real difference. Do you have a great idea for a new product or system improvement? We’re all ears!

Growing and global. We’re growing fast! We now have global presence across APAC, and Europe regions and we’re only getting started!

Work with a pack of awesome, genuine people who are passionate about what they do.

Grow your career with us. We’re big believers in lifelong learning. You’ll be given access to LinkedIn Learning, plus opportunities for internal mobility and leadership training to fast-track your career.

Pets our part of our family: bring your pet to our Crows Nest office, access our Pawrental leave when you adopt a new cat or dog, pet carer and compassionate leave.

Generous perks including day off for your anniversary, product discounts, volunteering days to help the community, novated leases, a rewards program and parental leave.

What’s next?


If you're ready to unleash your potential and make a real difference in the booming pet industry, then we want to hear from you! Next steps will include:

An initial telephone interview followed by 2 face to face interviews
2 work references
Background checks including Police, Qualification and Fraud Checks




We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. Diversity’s not a buzzword here, it’s in our DNA. Diverse perspectives shape our culture and make our work better. That’s why we’re committed to building inclusive teams that represent a variety of backgrounds and skills. If you need any reasonable adjustments, accessibility assistance or would like to note which pronouns you use at any stage of our hiring process, just contact us at accommodations: people&culture@realpetfoodco.com.au. We look forward to hearing from you.

Please note: NO agencies will be considered during this process. We encourage you to refrain from submitting unsolicited profiles

About the Role
This role supports a major multi-phase transition to a common SAP S/4HANA ERP environment. The focus is on preparing the business for upcoming upgrades, improving user experience and driving adoption across impacted teams. You will work closely with the Business Readiness Lead to deliver change, communications and readiness activities throughout the program.

Key Responsibilities
• Support business readiness assessments and follow up on actions to reduce resistance to change
• Review change impact analyses across stakeholder groups
• Assist in implementing business readiness and communications plans
• Coordinate readiness and change activities to ensure users are informed, prepared and supported
• Provide input into training materials and collaborate with training resources and SMEs
• Support risk mitigation related to readiness and change activities
• Implement reinforcement plans, monitor adoption and investigate any issues
• Prepare inputs for project, program and executive level reporting
• Draft content for newsletters, forums and internal updates
• Adhere to communication standards and ensure consistency across program materials
• Maintain alignment with other projects to ensure coordinated change activity

Essential Experience and Skills
• Demonstrated experience in stakeholder engagement and change-related activities
• Experience with or certification in recognised project or change methodologies
• Minimum 3 years of organisational change experience on large projects
• Experience supporting implementation of change and communications strategies
• Strong ability to support people through the change process
• Well developed relationship-building skills across varied locations
• Ability to work confidently with technical and non-technical teams
• Strong interpersonal and communication skills
• Customer-focused approach with the ability to build trust and credibility
• Able to self-manage, meet deadlines and work effectively in fast-paced environments
• Pragmatic, proactive and comfortable working independently or in dispersed teams
• Flexibility for occasional after hours work or domestic travel

Desirable
• Experience in the gas or energy sector
• Experience working in regulated environments


At Chandler Macleod, we are committed to fostering a diverse workforce where everyone is welcome. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, women, neurodiverse, people living with a disability and the LGBTIQA+ community.

You can read more about our commitment to diversity and inclusion at https://www.chandlermacleod.com/diversity-and-inclusion.

Job Title: Oracle ERP Finance Manager - Technology Implementation
Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Job Description

Continuous business transformation with technology is essential for organisations seeking to grow, increase efficiencies and remain relevant amid times of innovation and change. Our Technology Implementation team work closely with organisations to enhance the potential of their technology through the analysis, assessment, and implementation of proven technology solutions. Successful transformation is more than embedding new technology into a business. It requires deep industry insight, functional expertise and technology know-how that underpins an organisation’s strategic goals.

Your Opportunity

Forming part of the KPMG Oracle Cloud ERP team, you will play a key role of end to end project delivery lifecycle from initiation, to go-live, warranty, and support across multiple clients from a wide range of industries, by:

Working closely with the client, to understand, analyse and document their requirements and derive innovative solutions.

Leading workshops that enable the customer to understand the benefits and opportunities of the technology and how it can benefit the business, aligning to KPMG leading practices and cloud adoption.

Providing clear and concise configuration and other solution documentation (e.g. writing Functional Specifications).

Developing and expand own knowledge of Oracle Cloud and related applications through active self-learning, formal training and contribution to forums.

Assisting with presales activities and provide support, where required for the preparation of proposals and tenders.

Configuring Oracle Fusion Cloud ERP products, approvals and workflows, design and configure security roles, BI & OTBI reports, value sets, design studio and personalization.

How are you Extraordinary?

You are passionate about the importance of fantastic communication to share ideas, inspire, and create change. You are able to digest, distill, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal forms.

You get things done! You're proactive, results driven, and enjoy bringing your strengths to a multidisciplinary and impactful team.

You love being part of a collaborative and multidisciplinary team and building strong relationships both internally and externally.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and unique experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience could include: 

Recent implementation experience of an Oracle ERP Solution in a hands-on configuration role or as a business lead.

Experience in implementing, configuring or supporting at least four of the following Oracle Fusion ERP Cloud modules: General Ledger, Payables, Receivables, Asset Management, Payments & Collections, Cash and Expense Management, Project Portfolio Management, Procurement.

A great understanding of finance processes and practices and a demonstrated ability to interpret these into functional requirements.

Technical expertise in approvals and workflow configuration, designing and configuring Security Roles, BI & OTBI Reports, Value Sets, Design Studio and Personalization.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Investment Analyst, Performance and Risk Analytics
Ad Text:
Team Super is a leading industry superannuation fund servicing the transport, energy and mining industries across Australia, with over 150,000 members and more than $22bn of funds under management. Team Super was recognised by Money Magazine in 2025 as Best of the Best.

The Investment Analyst, Performance and Risk Analytics supports the Head of Investment Strategy delivering insights with a fund-wide perspective on investment performance and risk.

Responsibilities

Design and deliver data-driven analytics solutions

Develop and maintain insightful dashboards and other tools to visualise performance and risk metrics

Provide impactful performance reporting and attribution analysis across portfolios, asset classes, and investment options to support strategic decision-making

Produce clear, actionable risk reports and insights for diverse stakeholders, supporting a whole-of-portfolio risk management approach

Monitor whole-of-portfolio risk exposures including factor exposures, liquidity and derivatives and manage breaches against established limits

Develop and maintain internal and external performance and risk analytics systems and models, ensuring strong data governance (accuracy and integrity), to drive deeper portfolio insights

Collaborate with the Custodian to ensure its performance and risk reporting service is maximised

Automate and enhance reporting processes by replacing manual Excel models with scalable, integrated data solutions

Support innovation across the investment function by identifying opportunities to improve processes, reduce risk, and enhance cost efficiency

Qualifications

Business related tertiary qualification to support the scope of the position.

Postgraduate studies in a finance related field (commenced or completed) and/or a relevant industry qualification such as the CFA, CIPM, FRM or equivalent.

Skills and Experience

At least five years' experience in investments either with a fund manager, superannuation fund, custodian or related industry

A thorough understanding of financial markets, financial instruments (derivatives) and multi-asset class portfolios and their associated performance and risk metrics

Extensive experience in investment performance and risk analytics, including attribution

Proficiency with investment data and analytics vendors such as Bloomberg and FactSet ideal, or any alternative risk analytics platforms

Experience with data management and coding/programming tools such as Python and/or visualisation tools such as PowerBI

Advanced Excel modelling, analytical and problem-solving capabilities

Comprehensive knowledge of regulatory requirements for superannuation fund investment reporting

Business acumen and strong attention to detail

Excellent written and oral communication skills

Strong interpersonal skills with ability to build and maintain multi-level relationships

For more information about Team Super, please visit www.teamsuper.com

We look forward to your application.

The Opportunity

We’re looking for a Sustainability Reporting Manager to join our Group Sustainability team on a 12-month full-time fixed term contract covering parental leave. This is your chance to play a key role in delivering Stockland’s external sustainability reporting, compliance and systems management to make a real impact on how we share our ESG strategy and progress with the world.

You’ll lead the voluntary side of reporting, working closely with our passionate sustainability team, and manage the end-to-end reporting process – a project that that spans every part of our business. Giving you exposure to investment management, development, and enterprise functions. You’ll also be the main point of contact for our external assurance partner and environmental system manager.




What You’ll Do

Project manage Stockland’s annual ESG reporting suite, including ESG Data Pack and Management Approaches.

Coordinate external assurance and submissions for investor ESG surveys like GRESB and S&P CSA.

Manage our environmental data system (Envizi) and ensure compliance with National Greenhouse and Energy Reporting.

Build strong relationships across enterprise functions including People and Culture, Safety, Risk, Indigenous Engagement, Strategic Procurement and more.

Drive continuous improvement in sustainability governance, reporting and data management.




About You

You love working with data but can also engage and influence people. You thrive on managing complex projects and enjoy collaborating with diverse stakeholders. You’re looking for a role where you can combine technical expertise with relationship-building to deliver meaningful outcomes.




Experience & Skills That Count

Significant experience in sustainability reporting preferably within an ASX listed environment.

Strong project management skills and ability to manage long reporting cycles.

Experience with sustainability disclosure frameworks and external assurance processes.

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills.

Bonus points for experience with Envizi or similar environmental data systems.

Property sector experience is a nice-to-have.

The Right Mindset

Collaborative and curious – you’re always looking for ways to improve.

Comfortable working with data and systems while keeping the big picture in mind.

Organised and proactive – you know how to keep complex projects on track.




Why Stockland?

We’re a community: a supportive, empowered team that works as one to create better places and experiences for everyone, including ourselves. We’re committed to building an inclusive workplace where diverse perspectives are welcomed, and everyone feels a genuine sense of belonging. If you need adjustments during the recruitment process, just let us know.




Apply today and help us shape a better future.
Stockland – a better way to live.

About the role:

Seeking Enterprise & Data Governance Manager for our key local government client. This role oversees the strategic and operational management of our client's information assets, ensuring compliance with legislative and regulatory requirements while advancing records-management excellence and elevating data as a strategic organizational asset.
The position provides strategic direction and oversight for records lifecycle management, data governance practices, digital transformation initiatives, and the integration of data across departments to advance our client's business requirements and objectives.
Responsabilities:

Lead a high-performance, values-driven culture aligned with our client's Leadership Blueprint.
Develop and maintain data governance policies and frameworks that enable data-driven decisions and responsible AI use.
Ensure compliance with emerging privacy, AI governance, and cybersecurity requirements, proactively managing risks.
Oversee records lifecycle management and establish compliant retention schedules.
Implement and manage legal holds and ensure regulatory compliance across all information assets.
Manage physical and digital archives to ensure secure, efficient, and accessible record storage.
Lead document control processes and support audits related to information management.
Monitor compliance and provide regular reporting against internal and statutory requirements.
Support data quality and integration initiatives to ensure accurate, consistent, and reliable data sharing.

Requirements:

Experience contributing to digital transformation efforts and cross-department data integration projects.
Strong communication and leadership skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and senior stakeholders.
Relevant qualifications in information management, data governance, records management, or a related field.
If this sound like a role for you, apply now! Or feel free to reach out to Alan Kocjman - 07 3291 5401 / alan.kocjman@peoplebank.com.au for a confidential discussion





Peoplebank and Leaders IT are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone belongs. We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, identities, and experiences. If you need adjustments to the recruitment process due to your circumstances, please let us know—we’re here to support you.

About LEAP

LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Management Solutions in the world and is part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies. For more than 30 years, our curiosity and commitment to continual improvement has kept us reimagining productivity tools for lawyers and their staff to support our guiding purpose, to ‘Help lawyers who help people’. The market-leading software we develop, and support is used by more than 70,000 lawyers and their staff in small and medium-sized law firms.

Working alongside our international team of passionate high achievers, you’ll join a fast-growing technology business where things seldom stay the same for long. With more than 800 smart, caring and ambitious ‘LEAPsters’ working together across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland, Poland and New Zealand, you’ll find yourself in good company here.

Meet the Global Business Systems team

We’re a fast growing business built on a foundation of cutting edge technology and our Global Business Systems Teams are the sharp minds and steady hands keeping us running smoothly and making sure we’re always one step ahead. 

Whether you’re keeping user’s technology up to date, using analytics to solve complex business problems, or digitising processes to improve the ways we work, our technology specialists are the forward thinking experts keeping the engine of our continued success running – and the success of our clients too.  

If you’re a tech-savvy critical thinker with big ambitions and a passion to make an impact, you’ll discover not just a fulfilling career, but the opportunity to redefine the world of LegalTech. 

What you'll do

As our newest Analytics Engineer, you’ll be designing and scaling LEAP’s new enterprise data platform and semantic layer - the foundation for consistent metrics, AI enablement, and trusted insights that guide decisions across Executive, Product, Marketing, and Finance. This is a hands-on, engineering-focused role where you’ll partner closely with our BI Manager and Insight Analyst to ensure that metrics are standardised and data is accessible, trustworthy, and ready for both dashboards and advanced analytics. 

To make this happen, you will:

Build and maintain scalable, governed data models in dbt/Snowflake that power cross-functional reporting and advanced analytics. 
Develop and extend the universal semantic layer, ensuring metrics are consistent, reusable, and ready for both BI and AI applications. 
Structure high-quality, well-documented data assets that serve as the knowledge base for AI agents, predictive analytics, and self-service BI. 
Optimise and manage data pipelines (Fivetran/dbt) for reliability, performance and incremental refresh. 
Collaborate with the Data & Insights Analysts to translate the Metrics That Matter, a unified KPI framework across functions, into scalable, governed data models within the semantic layer. 
Ensure data quality and trust through testing, monitoring, and documentation.  

What you'll bring

Proficiency in SQL and modern data modelling (dbt preferred). 
Hands-on experience with Snowflake (or other cloud data warehouses). 
Familiarity with Fivetran (or similar ELT tools). 
Proven ability to design reusable, scalable data models that drive business outcomes. 
Experience integrating multiple data sources (Salesforce, Zuora, product usage, financial systems). 
Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to balance speed with governance. 
Experience with version control systems (Git preferred) and familiarity with CI/CD practices. 

Consider it a bonus if you have: 

Exposure to BI/visualisation tools (Tableau, Power BI, or similar). 
Experience with Python for data processing or automation. 
Interest in AI/ML integration (no need to be an expert yet). 

You are the type of person who

Has a collaborative, proactive mindset and you’re comfortable working in a fast-paced, evolving environment. 
Has strong communication skills, able to translate technical concepts into business outcomes. 
Is a self-starter attitude with a willingness to learn, experiment, and take ownership of tasks. 
Is a team player who understands that diverse opinions make a team and the benefit of achieving goals and decisions together. 
Is curious - you're not afraid to ask questions, explore and share your thoughts and ideas.  

LEAP is an inclusive, people-first company committed to breaking down institutional barriers that keep people from reaching their potential. If you meet some, but not all the requirements above, we encourage you to still submit your application.

Why join LEAP?

Your work matters. Helping lawyers help people sits at the heart of everything we do. We solve real world problems that improve and support local, everyday law firms. So they can do their best work for the people in the communities they serve.
Make an impact. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to be heard, to work on big & complex projects – and to make a real difference.
Work with a group of authentic, passionate people who love what they do.
Well-funded and global. LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Productivity Solutions across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland and New Zealand. We're part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies.
Flexible and hybrid working. We'd like to find this person in Sydney, but we want you to work in a way that suits you and we're open to flexible arrangements that support you.
Grow your career with us. Our founder Christian Beck has been building legal tech businesses for over 30 years. There are opportunities galore to expand your career based on where your interests lie. We're not afraid to pivot based on market conditions - you will always have the opportunity to stay ahead of the curve and do your best work here.
Have fun with us. Celebrations. Socials. Sports teams. Access to sailing and yacht events.
We value your well-being - enjoy an additional paid wellbeing day every year, free gym membership, corporate dental plan and monthly massages in the office. We'll throw in a catered lunch and breakfast every week too. Oh and an on-site barista.
Access to LEAP Home - a program unique to LEAP to support you in buying your primary residence.

Job Description

The Role

We’re looking for a Principal Data Scientist to set the technical direction for how we build end-to-end, data-driven products that create tangible value for hirers and job seekers. In this role, you’ll lead the design of the inference and decisioning layers across our most critical AI/ML products, shaping how SEEK understands supply and demand dynamics in the marketplace and informing high‑impact decisions across the business. You will be a force multiplier: developing technical strategy, uplifting standards and practices across multiple teams, and partnering closely with Product, Engineering, Strategy, and Commercial leaders to deliver measurable business outcomes.

You thrive in a complex, fast-moving environment and operate comfortably across ambiguity, aligning stakeholders on direction, navigating dependencies, shaping estimation and delivery plans, and communicating trade-offs clearly. You remain hands-on where it matters—diving deep into models, methods, and data quality—while cultivating a culture of continuous learning and scientific rigor across the Data Science community.

On any given day, you might:

Evaluate and guide the development of statistically sound, pragmatic models and decision systems, balancing performance, risk, and operational constraints.

Prototype and assess new approaches to unlock step-change improvements on core business problems, and articulate the value, assumptions, and limitations to senior stakeholders.

Partner with Product Managers, Strategy, Architecture, and Commercial teams to refine problem framing and align roadmaps to the highest value opportunities.

Collaborate with an Experimentation team to design, instrument, and interpret A/B and quasi-experiments; set best practices for causal inference and robust measurement.

Mentor and sponsor data scientists — reviewing methodologies, validating outputs, and raising standards for reliability, scalability, and ethical use.

Shape and guide end-to-end AI/ML solutions with Engineering and Product—spanning data readiness, simplicity, feature pipelines, model lifecycle, observability, and governance.

Your closest collaborators will include senior peers across the Data Science stream, stream leads who bring Data Science, Engineering, and Product perspectives to joint problem-solving, and squad leads driving contributions across SEEK’s broader AI initiatives. You will also influence cross-stream forums to ensure coherence in technical approaches and reuse of foundational capabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Define and evolve the technical strategy for a focus area (e.g., pricing, market position, ad performance), ensuring data and modelling work directly serve business outcomes and risk thresholds.

Build a deep understanding of SEEK’s data assets and systems and champion the data quality, observability, and documentation required for robust decisioning at scale.

Translate ambiguous, high-value business problems into actionable requirements, clarifying value, assumptions, and constraints; drive alignment on approach and success measures.

Establish and uphold modelling and experimentation standards (evaluation protocols, causal inference patterns, offline/online validation, guardrails) across multiple squads.

Provide technical leadership and coaching to data scientists and leads; review solution designs and code where appropriate; foster a culture of scientific rigor, safety, and learning.

Partner on roadmaps and OKRs, influencing prioritisation and sequencing across teams; balance exploration with reliability and scale in production environments.

Communicate complex concepts to a wide range of audiences—executives, Product, Engineering, and other functions—tailoring depth and framing to drive clear decisions.

Qualifications

Qualifications

Extensive (typically 10+ years) commercial experience building and evolving data-driven products, with deep, hands-on expertise in machine learning algorithms, decision systems, and model performance tuning at scale.

Proven track record operating as a bridge across Data Science, Product, Architecture, and Engineering, solving complex commercial problems and influencing strategy.

Experience leading through influence across multiple teams or managing a high-performing team of Data Scientists; delivery of large, complex, multi-stakeholder initiatives.

High proficiency with Python, SQL, and Spark for data extraction and processing; strong fluency with modern software practices and tooling (e.g., Git, AWS, Databricks, MLflow or equivalents).

Exceptional communication and stakeholder influence skills; ability to operate confidently amid ambiguity, set direction, and drive alignment across functions.

Comfortable in a *nix command-line environment; postgraduate qualification in a quantitative discipline (e.g., Physics, Mathematics, Bioinformatics, Computer Science, Engineering) or equivalent industry experience.
